Over 2 decades ago,  @lyonsshareart gallery in Fairhope, Alabama was the first gallery to represent me as an artist. In 2001, I had just graduated from Auburn and had no idea what to do with the pieces from my senior show. Mike and Kelley Lyons offered to sell them for me and thanks to them, my art career was launched! Their wonderful gallery is turning 45 this year, so to celebrate, the fabulous @kelleyb.ogburn and I are are having a show at the Lyons Share for the month of March (my favorite month in Fairhope! 🌸) The show officially kicks off this Friday night - 03.03.23. If you can’t join us at the show, please check out our art online. Just follow the link in my bio this Friday to see all of my new florals that will be up for grabs 🌸

Today is the big day! My new show titled “In the Morning Light” is now available at @anneirwinfineart 🤍 I’ve put so much time and love into each of these 32 pieces and I hope you will enjoy viewing them as much I enjoyed creating them!

Summer 2023 was one of my all time favorites! I took some time off from painting and my family and I did some traveling. I also made the leap to move my studio out of my house and into a (slightly) larger space downtown. My girls went back to school this week and I’ve kicked off my first true week of serious painting in my new studio. Starting over in this new and (somewhat) organized space feels great and I hope will lead to lots of cool new work for my upcoming fall shows!

This latest series “Shadow Song” was so much fun to create!They were an interesting departure from my usual multi-layered, multi-colored florals. It was refreshing to break down these studies of nasturtiums into 2 simple color combinations. For more details about these large pieces, click the link in my bio.

One of my favorite things about shows at @hillarywhitakergallery are these walls of framed paper pieces! I love the mixture of colorful art inside of these beautiful lucite frames 🤍

Just got home from one of the most incredible trips of my life! I was lucky enough to be one of 9 women to join designer Beth Dillard @notremaisondesigngroup (an American who now resides full-time in Goult, France) on a @foragingprovence experience. We explored dozens of gorgeous Provencal villages, foraged for truffles, rode ebikes from town to town, shopped at the marche in L’Isle-sur-laSorgue, dined in so many amazing restaurants, visited the home of Picasso’s partner Dora Maar, took a watercolor class with a local artist, had incredible nightly aperos and dinners catered by @mycateringprovence , and made wonderful friendships with all the women on the retreat! I highly recommend this experience to anyone who loves to travel and wants an authentic taste of Provence!
It’s so fun to be back in the studio painting things that inspired me on my recent travels. I couldn’t wait to paint these beautiful flowers we got from @terreduluberon84 in Provence ❤️

As someone who loves listening to podcasts, I was incredibly honored to be asked by the amazing @kellyannepowers to do an interview for her fabulous podcast: @learntopaintpodcast ! My episode goes live today, so please follow the link above to check it out. @learntopaintpodcast is such a great resource for anyone who likes to paint, whether you’re a beginner or have been painting professionally for decades. @kellyannepowers has interviewed a lot of my favorite current artists such as @zoeyfrank @melaniemorrisart @teddiparkerart @feliciaforte @fieldart @lynnwhipple and many, many others!
